FBIS3-45068 "drchi008_k_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political & Social Li Peng Inscribes for New Reform Newspaper OW1201080294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0725 GMT 12 Jan 94 OW1201080294 Beijing XINHUA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, January 12 (XINHUA) -- The first issue of CHINA'S REFORM, a newspaper specialising in reports on the country's ongoing policies of reform and opening to the outside, was published here today. Li Peng, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and premier of the State Council, wrote a congratulatory inscription for the newspaper. Li encouraged the paper to "emancipate the mind, seek truth from facts, and concentrate on quality reporting". Its first issue carries an article by State Councillor and Minister in Charge of the State Commission for Restructuring the Economy Li Tieying, entitled "Congratulations and Hope". The newspaper, published by the commission, will appear six times in the first two months, but starting from March will appear every Tuesday and Friday.
